name: Space Invaders II
overview: Space Invaders II is a fixed shooter arcade game which was released by Midway Games (in 1980); it utilizes an Intel 8080A microprocessor, running at 1.9968 MHz, and was created without authorization of Taito Corporation, who are the original creators for the Space Invaders series. Because the second official title in the series, Space Invaders Part II, was released in the U.S. as "Space Invaders Deluxe" as an update of the original, this American title was therefore given the naming of "Space Invaders II".
